touch — create empty files

SYNOPSIS
  touch FILE...

DESCRIPTION
  For each missing FILE, creates an empty file at that path. For files
  that already exist, touch is a no-op: OC's managed filesystem does
  not expose a way to update lastModified from Lua, so the POSIX
  "bump mtime" behaviour is not available here.

  Use the file's existence as the signal touch is meant to provide
  (e.g., for marker files like /etc/boot.selftest).

EXAMPLES
  touch /var/lib/marker         create the marker file
  touch a b c                   create three at once

SEE ALSO
  mkdir(1), rm(1)
